HEADWORD: Secretage
<hw>Se"cret*age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety> <def>A
process in which mercury, or some of its salts, is employed to impart
the property of felting to certain kinds of furs.</def>
<rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

